<s-function-doc>
<s-topics>
  <s-topic>vgm</s-topic>
</s-topics>

<s-title>
Generate, or Add to Variogram Model
</s-title>

<s-description>
Generates a variogram model, or adds to an existing model. 
<s-expression>print.variogram.model</s-expression> prints the essence of a variogram  model.
</s-description>

<s-usage>
<s-old-style-usage>
vgm(psill, model, range, nugget, add.to, anis, kappa = 0.5)
print.variogram.model(x, ...)
</s-old-style-usage>
</s-usage>

<s-args>
<s-arg name="psill">
(partial) sill of the variogram model component </s-arg>
<s-arg name="model">
model type, e.g. "Exp", "Sph", "Gau", "Mat". Calling vgm() without
a model argument returns the list with available models. </s-arg>
<s-arg name="range">
range of the variogram model component </s-arg>
<s-arg name="kappa">
smoothness parameter for the Matern class of variogram 
models </s-arg>
<s-arg name="nugget">
nugget component of the variogram (this basically adds a nugget
compontent to the model) </s-arg>
<s-arg name="add.to">
a variogram model to which we want to add a component </s-arg>
<s-arg name="anis">
anisotropy parameters: </s-arg>
<s-arg name="x">
a variogram model to print </s-arg>
<s-arg name="...">
arguments that will be passed to <s-expression>print</s-expression>, e.g. <s-expression>digits</s-expression>
(see examples) </s-arg>
</s-args>

<s-value>
an object of class variogram.model, which extends data.frame Calling 
<s-expression>vgm</s-expression> without a model argument returns the list with available models.
</s-value>

<s-section name="AUTHOR(S)">
Edzer J. Pebesma
</s-section>

<s-section name="REFERENCES">

</s-section>

<s-see>
<s-function name="print.variogram.model">print.variogram.model</s-function>, 
